        "a": "Because you as the landlord pay operating expenses directly, your NOI equals gross rent collected minus those expenses. Any increase in taxes, insurance, or maintenance reduces your NOI dollar for dollar unless your lease includes an expense stop or pass-through clause. Accurate expense forecasting at lease underwriting is essential to protecting your returns on a gross-leased property."
